This paper deals with the task of object localization in medical images, specifically chest X-ray images. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain. The paper proposes a novel loss function and a new architecture for tackling this problem, which involves weakly supervised learning. This suggests that the paper could also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) domains. The paper also mentions the use of CRF layers and anti-aliasing filters, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) domains, respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IR.
